# Pull requests

When creating or drafting a pull request for this repository (including via `gh pr create`):

1. Read and follow **`.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`** — the PR title and body must include every section from that template: **Summary**, **Type of change** (checkboxes), **Changes**, **How to test**, and **Checklist** (checkboxes).
2. Fill each section with concrete, accurate detail (what changed, why, how to verify, risk notes). Do not submit a one-line PR description.
3. Prefer `gh pr create --body-file` with a complete body, or paste the filled template into `--body`, so GitHub receives the full structure.

The template is the single source of truth for PR format in this project.
